results.name: Number of primes between prime(n)*prime(n+1) and prime(n+1)^2.
link: Antti Karttunen, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..6541
example: For n=1, there is only one prime in range prime(1)*prime(2) .. prime(2)^2, [6 .. 9], namely 7, thus a(1) = 1.
For n=2, the primes in range prime(2)*prime(3) .. prime(3)^2, [15 .. 25] are {17, 19, 23}, thus a(2) = 3.
mathematica: Table[Count[Range[Prime[n] Prime[n + 1], Prime[n + 1]^2], _?PrimeQ], {n, 69}] (* _Michael De Vlieger_, Mar 30 2015 *)
program: (Scheme) (define (A256469 n) (let* ((p (A000040 n)) (q (A000040 (+ 1 n))) (q2 (* q q))) (let loop ((s 0) (k (* p q))) (cond ((= k q2) s) (else (loop (+ s (if (prime? k) 1 0)) (+ k 1)))))))
